At the moment there is a lot of inline URL construction in the Studio plugins. For example, in {{NavbarRenderer}}:

{code}
map.put("updateStatusUrl", studioNavbarInformation.getConfluenceBaseUrl() + "/display/~" + studioNavbarInformation.getUserName());
{code}

Sometimes this construction is repeated in different places. It would be nice if this were externalised in some way.

The chatbar JSESSIONID is not being set to the correct domain.  This appears to be a regression, as the domain was set correctly in 2.1.  What this results in is every time the chatbar is loaded into a page, a new chatbar session is created because the host is different (due to our DNS aliasing).  Most browsers only support a maximum of 20 cookies per domain, and so eventually the browser drops the crowd cookie, and the user is logged out.

The best solution to this problem is to investigate tomcats support of cookie domains, I know current releases of Tomcat 6 now support setting the domain.

If that's not an option, then fixing the code that we originally wrote to overwrite the domain is the next best thing.

As a work around before we are able to push out a new release of JIRA Studio, we will disable DNS aliasing in affected instances.  To do this, in the following files:

* {{/opt/jirastudio/build/current/jira/WEB-INF/classes/studio.default.properties}}
* {{/opt/jirastudio/build/current/confluence/WEB-INF/classes/studio.default.properties}}
* {{/opt/jirastudio/build/current/bamboo/WEB-INF/classes/studio.default.properties}}
* {{/opt/jirastudio/build/current/fisheye/studio.default.properties}}

On the following line:

{noformat}
chatbar.comet.base.url=http://chat{alias}.XXXXX.jira.com:8000/chatbar
{noformat}

Remove the {{\{alias\}}} token, eg:

{noformat}
chatbar.comet.base.url=http://chat.XXXXX.jira.com:8000/chatbar
{noformat}

A restart will be required of JIRA, Confluence, FishEye and Bamboo for the above changes to take effect.

The consequence of this workaround is that the chatbar will stop working for a user if that user has 6 or more JIRA Studio tabs open in their browser.
